Yannas v. Frondistou\u2011Yannas, 395 Ma.proposition:
The best interests of the child is the “paramount” and governing standard in all custody and parenting‑time determinations and modifications in Massachusetts. See, e.g.:

   - Yannas v. Frondistou‑Yannas, 395 Mass. 704, 710 (1985);  
   - Custody of Kali, 439 Mass. 834, 840–41 (2003);  
   - Custody of a Minor, 389 Mass. 755, 766–67 (1983).

