Schuler v. Schuler, 382 Mass. 366, 368\u.proposition:
A party seeking modification of a prior custody or parenting‑time order must show a material and substantial change in circumstances since entry of the last judgment, and that modification is in the child’s best interests. See, e.g.:

   - Schuler v. Schuler, 382 Mass. 366, 368–69 (1981);  
   - Bouchard v. Bouchard, 12 Mass. App. Ct. 899, 899–900 (1981);  
   - Ardizoni v. Raymond, 40 Mass. App. Ct. 734, 738 (1996).

